text: Dean Ebbe (born 16 July 1994) is an Irish professional footballer who plays as a striker for the Welsh Premier League side The New Saints. ==Career== After playing for Shamrock Rovers, Longford Town, Athlone Town, Cabinteely, Collinstown and Bluebell United, Ebbe signed for Scottish club Inverness Caledonian Thistle in January 2017. After leaving Inverness he returned to Bluebell United before signing for Welsh Premier League side The New Saints in January 2018. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Republic of Ireland association footballers Category:Shamrock Rovers F.C. players Category:Longford Town F.C. players Category:Athlone Town A.F.C. players Category:Cabinteely F.C. players Category:Bluebell United F.C. players Category:Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C. players Category:The New Saints F.C. players Category:League of Ireland players Category:Scottish Professional Football League players Category:Cymru Premier players Category:Association football forwards Category:Republic of Ireland expatriate association footballers Category:Irish expatriate sportspeople in Scotland Category:Expatriate footballers in Scotland Category:Irish expatriate sportspeople in Wales Category:Expatriate footballers in Wales
